li
	h4.subtitle 2.2.4 - Distance Matrix
	p In addition to the Tree Visualization to represent distances between nodes, PHYLOViZ Online also offers the interactive <b><i>Distance Matrix</i></b> visualization, which represents the <i>All vs All</i> distances between nodes selected from the <b>Tree</b> tab using <a href="#selection">Node selection</a>. It also displays information about each comparison and t is possible to order the matrix data according to the existing fields in the auxiliary data.
	br
	div(style="width:100%; text-align:center;")
		img(id="matrix1" href="/images/matrix1.png" style="width:40%; height: auto;" src="/images/matrix1.png")
	ul
		li
			div.tutorialsubsections(id="compute")
				h5 Compute distances
				table
					tr.subrow
						td.tutorialcolumns
							img(id="compute1" href="/images/compute1.png" style="width:60%; height: auto;" src="/images/compute1.png")
						td.othercolumns
							<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span>
						td(style="text-align:justify")
							p The distance matrix is not generated by default. To create the matrix there is a <i>need to <a href="#selection">select some nodes</a></i> in the Tree Visualization. After node selection, users can click on the <b><i>Compute distances</i></b> button, located at the <b>Operations</b> menu, that will redirect them to <b><i>Distances</i></b> tab of the application.
		li
			div.tutorialsubsections(id="order")
				h5 Order
				table
					tr.subrow
						td.tutorialcolumns
							img(id="order1" href="/images/order1.png" style="width:60%; height: auto;" src="/images/order1.png")
						td.othercolumns
							<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span>
						td(style="text-align:justify")
							p By default, the <b>Matrix</b> is ordered <i>by identifier</i>. However, Users can choose to order it <i>by some field present in the auxilary data</i>. This allows positioning of nodes with the same values closer together and facilitates the cluster visualization.
		li
			div.tutorialsubsections(id="select")
				h5 Select/Export
				table
					tr.subrow
						td.tutorialcolumns
							img(id="selectexport2" href="/images/selectexport2.png" style="width:60%; height: auto;" src="/images/selectexport2.png")
						td.othercolumns
							<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span>
						td(style="text-align:justify")
							p On <i>mouse over</i> the distance matrix cells, information associated with them is displayed in the information table. Users can see the distance between pairs of nodes and their auxiliary data, which <b>fields can be filtered using the checkboxes above the table</b>. Multiple selections can be made and stored in the table for analysis. 
					tr.subrow
						td.tutorialcolumns
							img(id="selectexport1" href="/images/selectexport1.png" style="width:60%; height: auto;" src="/images/selectexport1.png")
						td.othercolumns
							<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span>
						td(style="text-align:justify")
							p Information displayed in the table can also be exported in the way of <i>two files</i>: <b>profile</b> and <b>auxiliary data</b> file. Only information from selected cells is exported.


